{
  "texts": [
    "Inserting into the minimization problem 6, and noting that the form of the term in inside the sum can be written [101,29,28]1 2σ 2 t ∥μ t (x t, x 0) -µ θ (x t, t)∥ 2 + C(13)for some C independent of the parameters θ.",
    "By itself, this is suitable for optimization, but we can go one step further, using the reparameterization trick mentioned in 3.1 [26].",
    "We separate the noise from the data to getx t (x 0, ϵ) = √ ᾱt x 0 + ϵ √ 1 -ᾱt (14)where ϵ is distributed with a standard unit (multi-dimensional) normal.",
    "It turns out that predicting ϵ leads to better results.",
    "Finally, we getβ 2 t 2σ 2 t α t (1 -ᾱt) ∥ϵ -ϵ θ (x t (x 0, ϵ), t)∥ 2(15)for our minimization objective."
  ]
}